ell lines and transfections. K562 cells (ATCC) were maintained in RPMI 1640 (Hyclone) supplemented with 10% bovine growth serum, 100 units/ml penicillin, 100 Βµg/ml streptomycin and 2 mM L-glutamine. K562s were transfected by nucleofection (Lonza) using program T-016 and a nucleofection buffer containing 100 mM KH2PO4, 15 mM NaHCO3, 12 mM MgCl2 β€Ά 6 H20, 8 mM ATP, 2 mM glucose, pH 7.4. HEK293T cells were maintained in DMEM (Cellgro) supplemented with 10% bovine growth serum, 100 units/ml penicillin, 100 Βµg/ml streptomycin and 2 mM L-glutamine. HEK293T cells were transfected either by calcium phosphate or Lipofectamine 2000 (Invitrogen).Nuclease and targeting vector constructionΞ²-globin NK TALENs were synthesized (Genscript) using the Ξ”152 N-terminal domain and the +63 C terminal domain previously described (13) and fused to the FokI nuclease domain and cloned into pcDNA3.1 (Invitrogen). Ξ²-globin NN TALENs and Ξ³-globin NN TALENs were synthesized using a Golden Gate cloning strategy (23) and cloned with the same N- and C- termini and nuclease domain into pcDNA3.1. The Ξ²-globin ZFNs were synthesized using the B2H selection strategy previously described (24). The Ξ²-Ubc-GFP targeting vector was synthesized by PCR amplifying arms of homology from genomic DNA isolated from K562 cells using the primers in Supplementary Figure S10 and cloning a Ubc-GFP expression cassette in between the arms. The Ξ²-in-frame-cDNA and Ξ²-in-frame-GFP targeting vectors were synthesized by overlap PCR to insert Ξ²-globin cDNA (OriGene) or GFP directly in-frame to the Ξ²-globin ATG start codon using the primers in Supplementary Figure S10. Silent mutations were introduced into the Ξ²-globin cDNA sequence at every sixth base pair between the nuclease cut site and the end of exon 1. The MGMT P140K drug selection cassette (generous gift from Dr Stan Gerson) was cloned into the targeting vector inside the arms of homology. The Ξ³-in-frame-tdTomato targeting vector was generated by genomic PC