s were used to characterize the Ξ²-globin nucleases because of the presence of a naturally occurring SNP in K562s.SMRT sequencing and cDNA targetingPCR products prior to cutting by the Surveyor nuclease were prepared for SMRT sequencing following the manufacturerβ€™s protocol (Pacific Biosciences). For the SMRT sequencing of the Ξ²-globin cDNA targeting events, 106 K562s were nucleofected with 10 Βµg Ξ²-in-frame-cDNA and 1 Βµg each of Ξ²L4 and Ξ²R4 TALENs. Aliquots were removed after 3 days when the first round of selection was begun by adding 50 ΒµM O6BG (Sigma) for 1 hour and then adding 40 ΒµM BCNU (Sigma) for 1 hour before changing the media. Cells were allowed to recover for 7β€“10 days at which time another aliquot was harvested and another round of selection started. Genomic DNA was isolated (Qiagen) and the Ξ²-globin region was PCR amplified using primers in Supplementary Figure S10, which did not amplify random integrants. Primers with unique 3 bp tags were used in the PCR reactions from each time point, such that the samples could be combined and analysed in one SMRT sequencing reaction. Data were analysed using CLC Genomics Workbench software.Generation of fluorescent reporter cell lines106 K562 cells were nucleofected with 10 Βµg of the targeting vector and 1 Βµg of each TALEN. Ξ²-globin-GFP cells were enriched by four rounds of selection with O6BG and BCNU and clones were established by limiting dilution. Ξ³-globin-tdTomato cells were enriched by treatment with 500 Βµg/ml G418 and clones were established by limiting dilution. Targeting was confirmed by genomic PCR spanning the integration junctions using primers in Supplementary Figure S10.Quantitative real-time PCRClonal populations of Ξ²-globin-GFP cells and Ξ³-globin-tdTomato cells which were targeted at one allele were treated for 4 days with 400 ΒµM hydroxyurea and total mRNA was harvested by Trizol/chloroform extraction and purified on RNeasy columns (Qiagen). 1 Βµg total RNA was used to synthesize cDNA with the iScript cDNA kit (Bio-Rad) following the manufacturerβ€™s protocol. Biological triplicates were each assayed in triplicate by qRT-PCR using SYBR green (Applied Biosystems) on a CFX384 real-time thermocycler (Bio-Rad) using the primers in Supplementary Figure S10 using the following conditions: initial denaturation (3 min at 95Β°C), 3-step PCR cycle (10 s at 95Β°C, 30 s at 55Β°C, 5 s at 65Β°C, 40 cycles). PCR efficiency (between 91% and 119%) was calculated using serial dilutions of template for each primer set. mRNA expression was quantified using the 2β�’Ξ”Ξ”Ct method as compared to the housekeeping gene GAPDH.Screening globin-modulating compoundsΞ²-globin-GFP cells and Ξ³-globin-tdTomato cells were treated for 4 days with the indicated concentrations of GTP (Sigma), GDP (Sigma), GMP (Sigma), guanosine (Sigma), guanine (Sigma), cGMP (Sigma), Decitabine (Sigma), Sodium butyrate (Sigma), hydroxyurea (Sigma), zileuton (Sigma), hemin (Sigma), cisplatin (Santa Cruz Biotech), pomalidomide (Sigma), mithramycin (Fisher), apicidin (Sigma), cytarabine (Sigma) or phenylacetate (Sigma). Fluorescence was measured using an Accuri C6 cytometer (Accuri), and was reported as the fold change in fluorescence intensity after 4 days.Statistical analysisData from at least three samples were used to determine significance by statistical analysis. Mean Β± SD is reported. Statistical significance was determined by Studentβ€™s t-test and P-values < 0.05 were considered significant.
